hps[hps == -99] <- NA

hps$PARTINARTS_num <- as.numeric(hps$PARTINARTS, levels = c("Strongly Agree", "Agree", "Disagree", "Strongly Disagree"), labels = c(1, 2, 3, 4))

hps$ANXIOUS <- factor(hps$ANXIOUS, levels = c(1, 2, 3, 4), labels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"))

hps$ANXIOUS_num <- as.numeric(hps$ANXIOUS, levels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"), labels = c(1, 2, 3, 4))

hps$WORRY <- factor(hps$WORRY, levels = c(1, 2, 3, 4), labels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"))

hps$WORRY_num <- as.numeric(hps$WORRY, levels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"), labels = c(1, 2, 3, 4))

hps$INTEREST <- factor(hps$INTEREST, levels = c(1, 2, 3, 4), labels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"))

hps$INTEREST_num <- as.numeric(hps$INTEREST, levels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"), labels = c(1, 2, 3, 4))

hps$DOWN <- factor(hps$DOWN, levels = c(1, 2, 3, 4), labels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"))

hps$DOWN_num <- as.numeric(hps$DOWN, levels = c("Not At All", "Several Days", "More Than Half The Days", "Nearly Every Day"), labels = c(1, 2, 3, 4))

hps$LIVENTERTAINMENT <-factor(hps$LIVENTERTAINMENT, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("Yes", "No"))

hps$LIVENTERTAINMENT_num <- as.numeric(hps$LIVENTERTAINMENT, levels = c("Yes", "No"), labels = c(1, 2))

hps$ARTEXHIBIT <-factor(hps$ARTEXHIBIT, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("Yes", "No"))

hps$ARTEXHIBIT_num <- as.numeric(hps$ARTEXHIBIT, levels = c("Yes", "No"), labels = c(1, 2))

hps$MOVIES <-factor(hps$MOVIES, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("Yes", "No"))

hps$MOVIES_num <- as.numeric(hps$MOVIES, levels = c("Yes", "No"), labels = c(1, 2))

hps$CREATEART_num <-as.numeric(hps$CREATEART, levels = c("Yes", "No"), labels = c(1, 2))

anx_by_create <- aggregate(
  ANXIOUS_num ~ CREATEART_num,
  data = hps,
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
worr_by_create <- aggregate(
  WORRY_num ~ CREATEART_num,
  data = hps, 
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
int_by_create <- aggregate(
  INTEREST_num ~ CREATEART_num,
  data = hps, 
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
down_by_create <- aggregate(
  DOWN_num ~ CREATEART_num,
  data = hps, 
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
anx_by_part <- aggregate(
  ANXIOUS_num ~ PARTINARTS_num,
  data = hps,
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
worr_by_part <- aggregate(
  WORRY_num ~ PARTINARTS_num,
  data = hps, 
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
int_by_part <- aggregate(
  INTEREST_num ~ PARTINARTS_num,
  data = hps, 
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)
down_by_part <- aggregate(
  DOWN_num ~ PARTINARTS_num,
  data = hps, 
  FUN = mean,
  na.rm = TRUE
)

#Anxious
hps$ANX_CAT <- ifelse(hps$ANXIOUS_num >= 3, "More", "Less")
hps$ANX_CAT <- factor(hps$ANX_CAT)

anx_createart_table <- table(hps$CREATEART_num, hps$ANX_CAT)
print(chisq.test(anx_createart_table))
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  anx_createart_table
## X-squared = 6.6756, df = 1, p-value = 0.009774
anx_partart_table <- table(hps$PARTINARTS_num, hps$ANX_CAT)
print(chisq.test(anx_partart_table))
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  anx_partart_table
## X-squared = 111.77, df = 3, p-value < 2.2e-16
